    "sections": [
      {
        "__typename": "StaticContentBlockRecord",
        "id": "94033600",
        "title": "Uses",
        "text": "A running list of the hardware, software, and tools I rely on day to day for building and shipping full stack applications and distributed systems.\n\n## Editor & Terminal\n\n- **Editor:** Visual Studio Code, with the standard TypeScript/ESLint/Prettier toolchain\n- **Terminal:** iTerm2 / Windows Terminal with zsh and Oh My Zsh\n- **Shell tools:** ripgrep, fzf, tmux\n- **Version control:** Git + GitHub CLI\n\n## Languages & Frameworks\n\n- **Frontend:** TypeScript, React, Next.js, Vue.js\n- **Backend:** Node.js, Python (FastAPI, Django)\n- **Databases:** PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis\n\n## Infrastructure & DevOps\n\n- **Cloud:** AWS (EC2, Lambda, RDS, S3)\n- **Containers & orchestration:** Docker, Kubernetes\n- **CI/CD:** GitHub Actions, Netlify\n\n## Design & Productivity\n\n- **Design:** Figma\n- **API testing:** Postman / Insomnia\n- **Notes & docs:** Notion\n\n## Hardware\n\n- Laptop: MacBook Pro (M-series)\n- External display: 4K monitor\n- Keyboard & mouse: mechanical keyboard, ergonomic mouse\n\nThis list evolves as tools change — check back for updates."
      }
    ],
